[Nouns] simplicity; plainness, homeliness; undress, chastity.
[Verbs] be simple
render simple; simplify.
[Adjectives] simple, plain; homely, homespun; ordinary, household.
unaffected; free from affectation, free from ornament; simplex munditiis [Horace]; sans facon, en deshabille.
chaste, inornate, severe.
unadorned, unornamented, undecked, ungarnished, unarranged, untrimmed, unvarnished.
bald, flat, dull.
